  "prompt": "What's the average number of answers to each question on Quora?",
  "response": "It's difficult to get a perfectly accurate number for the average number of answers per question on Quora for a few reasons:\n\n*   **Quora doesn't publicly release this statistic.** They don't have a publicly available API or dashboard that provides this average.\n*   **It changes over time.** As Quora grows and changes its algorithms, the average response rate can fluctuate.\n*   **It varies greatly by topic.** Questions on popular, general topics tend to get more answers than very niche or obscure topics.\n*   **\"Dead\" questions exist.** There are many questions on Quora that were asked years ago and have received no answers or very few views. These would skew the average downwards.\n\n**Estimates and Observations:**\n\nGiven the factors above, it is hard to pinpoint the exact average number of responses to a question on Quora. But considering active questions that are visible to the general public:\n\n* Some questions get 50+ answers.\n* Some questions get just 1 or 2 answers.\n* Some questions go unanswered.\n\n**Conclusion:**\n\nWhile a precise number is unavailable, it's fair to say that the average number of answers per question on Quora is somewhere between **1 and 5.**",
